name: Sunset Beauties
description:
Says Mama to her babe; The ways of the world are through my eyes now The things I show you are the things you see But one day, too soon for me, you will reach your own heights Eat your own leaves, and paint your own sunsets Go forth, and colour your world my love.
repeat 200 cm

name: Ewes Are Hot
description:
Girls are pink and boys are blue Ewes are hot and so are you.
repeat 49 cm

name: The Gathering Gentleman - Panel
description:
One of nature's finest seducers, the male bowerbird, awaits his lady. After the careful gathering, building and placement of his bursts of blue this satin gentleman is ripe and ready to perform. He will lure his mate into his cavernous nest and offer her all he has. This beautiful ritual of love, dance and courtship is meant for everlasting textile art.
repeat 190 cm

description:

name: Bright Sparks
description:
As she wanders through her home of blue gums and eucalypts, light, white, bright sparks flash through the hues of blues and greens. She feels comfort knowing she is not alone. Her spirits are lighting her way.
repeat 120 cm

name: Foxy Kinda Night - Panel
description:
Once every 76 years there is a special kind of night when the moon splashes light of magic upon us all. On this night the foxes come out to play, the sky is filled with rainbow stars, and the earth dances under the moons spell.
repeat 150 cm

description:
This wildly colourful print is a collage of Penny's favourite wildflower photos.

This scarf in silk satin georgette has a luxurious soft drape.
size 100 cm x 100 cm

name: Scarf - Orchids
description:
Australian native orchids occur mostly in the temperate forests of the Great Dividing Range which spans the length of the eastern coast of Australia. This exotic flower inspired Penny to create a collage print of her favourites.

This scarf in silk satin georgette has a luxurious soft drape.
size 100 cm x 100 cm

name: Scarf - Bottle Brush
description:
On a trip to Blackheath in the world heritage listed Blue Mountains region, Penny stopped by the side of the road at Woodford to photograph a beautiful bottle brush tree. The unique bristled flower of the bottle brush tree is one of Penny’s favourites.

This scarf in silk satin georgette has a luxurious soft drape.
size 100 cm x 100 cm

name: Banksia
description:
Blackheath is home to Porters Pass, one of the oldest tracks in the Blue Mountains dating back to 1888. This print is inspired by photos of the banksia taken before and after bushfires on this well worn track.
repeat 50 cm

name: Florescence
description:
The design of the print was initially inspired by the sculptural form, structure and vibrancy of the colourful Orchid flower. Together Lauren and Amelia photographed the Orchid from their grandmother's backyard. With the influence of the sculptural yet fluid form of the flower, they were able to mimic the shapes of the petals and transform the silhouette into a made to measured tailored jacket. The print plays with manipulating sections of the flower and colour variations that enhances the symmetrical print placement and pattern making of the jacket design.
repeat 161 cm

name: Peeling Paint - Ruby
description:
The Blue Mountains region in New South Wales is well known for its grand historic homes and cosy cottages with gorgeous cottage gardens. Visiting the area to photograph these homes and their interiors, the peeling paint on an old kitchen chimney was captured. This photo from a weatherboard house built in 1919 has inspired this wonderfully mottled and textured print.
repeat 100 cm

name: Peeling Paint - Sapphire
description:
The Blue Mountains region in New South Wales is well known for its grand historic homes and cosy cottages with gorgeous cottage gardens. Visiting the area to photograph these homes and their interiors, the peeling paint on an old kitchen chimney was captured. This photo from a weatherboard house built in 1919 has inspired this wonderfully mottled and textured print.
repeat 100 cm

name: Maldon - Jacaranda
description:
In country Victoria the historic gold rush town of Maldon is home to perfectly preserved buildings. This print was inspired by the peeling floral wallpaper in the old pub hallway and modernised by enlarging the design. The colours were chosen to remind us of the stunning leadlight light windows.
repeat 107 cm

name: Vintage Brocade
description:
I wanted to replicate the floral theme seen in the Eastern European floral wood carvings. Here I have used bright greens and warm reds.
repeat 43 cm

name: Russian Roses
description:
Inspired by the floral patterns on traditional Russian shawls and their most beloved motif, the rose.
repeat 70 cm

name: Russian Brocade
description:
I have taken inspiration from Russian floral patterns and reworked them to create this modern graphic floral print with folkloric overtones.
repeat 48 cm

name: Ink
description:
For a long time I have been interested in the technique of Japanese ink marbling. This design is a contemporary version using my own ink marble artworks, shaping them into a modern geometric print.
repeat 35 cm

name: Floral Triangle - Black & White
description:
Deconstructed hand drawing of garden flowers were used create this geometric triangle print.
repeat 34 cm

name: Floral Triangle
description:
Deconstructed hand drawing of garden flowers were used create this geometric triangle print.
repeat 34 cm

name: Floral Sketch
description:
Detailed hand drawings of garden flowers mixed with bold shapes to create depth in this print.
repeat 30 cm

name: Flora
description:
Inspired by an Autumn garden, this print uses floral illustrations with loose and delicate lines. I have also used watercolour markings and soft pastel colours to portray this feminine Autumn design.
repeat 56 cm

name: Eggs
description:
Growing up in Sweden we used to paint eggs to celebrate Easter. This print is my graphic interpretation of an traditional Easter egg painting session.
repeat 28 cm

name: Drake
description:
This print was inspired by the book “Bröderna Lejonhjärta”, ‘The Brothers Lionheart’ - which was written by one of my favorite childhood authors, Astrid Lindgren. I used the the evil dragon from the book as a inspiration for my motif.
repeat 30 cm

name: Paperbirds
description:
This print was designed with the Swedish winter in mind, bare trees, birds leaving for warmer climates, crisp blue skies and the colours of the sun being reflected in the white snow. I have used two different techniques to create ‘Paperbirds’; paper collage and linoleum print.
repeat 66 cm

name: Cherry Blossom
description:
Expressive and fluid watercolour florals inspired this cherry blossom print. It was about petal power, I wanted to create something artistic and abstract.
repeat 70 cm

name: Cous Cous - Gold
description:
A long time ago on a trip to Morocco, Doris was spellbound by the colour and intricacies of the tiles that seemed to adorn every wall and floor. This design is a reminder of this trip, and is inspired from the photos and the colours in Morocco.
repeat 40 cm

name: Cous Cous
description:
A long time ago on a trip to Morocco, Doris was spellbound by the colour and intricacies of the tiles that seemed to adorn every wall and floor. This design is a reminder of this trip, and is inspired from the photos and the colours in Morocco.
repeat 40 cm

name: Painted Stripe - Grey
description:
Gentle brush strokes of watercolour and ink have created this striking modern version of the humble stripe. This print looks stunning on a bikini or resort wear and is equally beautiful in the home.
repeat 65 cm

name: Painted Stripe - Navy
description:
Gentle brush strokes of watercolour and ink have created this striking modern version of the humble stripe. This print looks stunning on a bikini or resort wear and is equally beautiful in the home.

name: Painted Stripe - Red
description:
Gentle brush strokes of watercolour and ink have created this striking modern version of the humble stripe. This print looks stunning on a bikini or resort wear and is equally beautiful in the home.

name: Howell’s Farm Walls
description:
Inside Howell's Farm House on Maria Island built in 1923, the walls are lined with old wooden crates. Over the year’s layer upon layer of newspapers, letters and wall papers have been stuck on to fill gaps and decorate the rustic walls. The old house is still intact but over the years since the farm was last occupied, the wallpaper and newspaper have started to peel, leaving stunning a decopage of textures and patterns. This design was created from the photos taken of these walls.
repeat 60 cm

name: Tin Roof - Blue
description:
Robey's old farm property on Maria Island, off the east coast of Tasmania, has a wonderful old rusty iron shed. This design is inspired from a photo taken on that visit to the farm.
repeat 40 cm

name: Tin Roof
description:
Robey's old farm property on Maria Island, off the east coast of Tasmania, has a wonderful old rusty iron shed. This design is inspired from a photo taken on that visit to the farm.
repeat 40 cm

description:

repeat 107 cm

name: Roses
description:
We are fascinated by old un-renovated homes and stories the walls have to tell. This peeling wallpaper and what it revealed beneath has been reworked into this stunning panel print.
panel 275 cm

name: Seashells
description:
Walking along the north eastern coastline of Tasmanian in the Bay of Fires region it is not uncommon to happen upon a shell midden. The textures and colours of these shell mounds inspired this print.
repeat 83 cm

name: Bay of Fires
description:
The north eastern coast of Tasmania is home to be stunning Bay of Fires. Walking around the coastline you can't help but be drawn in by its serenity and weather-worn beauty. We are inspired by the crystalline quality of the light in Tasmania and have merged this with the rugged cracked rocks and boulders lining the coast to create this beautiful print.
repeat 103 cm

name: Barnacle
description:
The north eastern coast of Tasmania is home to the stunning Bay of Fires. Walking around the coastline you can't help but be drawn in by its serenity and weather-worn beauty. Black and blue tinged barnacles cover the rocks in this area and Doris and Maria pay homage to their rustic charm.
repeat 80 cm

name: Tin Shed
description:
Whilst Doris was exploring the rich convict history of Maria Island off the east coast of Tasmania, she came across interesting textures and details in the convict buildings and ruins. This print of old tin sheds is the first in a series to be inspired by the convict history of Maria Island.
repeat 67 cm

name: Maria
description:
Maria loves to travel and on a recent trip to Vietnam stumbled upon a charming temple in a small dusty town. It was not a tourist attraction and spoilt by the teeming masses, it just served the local people as a place of worship. The temples walls were covered in a mosaic of broken tiles from the past and loving applied to form wonderful patterns. Maria loved the effect and upon delving into the archives thought this mosaic of a flower would translate into a beautiful print.
repeat 125 cm

name: Casablanca
description:
A long time ago on a trip to Morocco, Doris was spellbound by the colour and intricacies of the tiles that seemed to adorn every wall and floor. This design is a reminder of this trip, and are inspired from the photos and the colours in Morocco.
repeat 25 cm

name: Algiers
description:
A long time ago on a trip to Morocco, Doris took a sojourn to Algiers and found beautiful tiles adorning wall and floors everywhere. She was mesmerised by the intricacy and colour of these tiles and this design is a reminder of that trip and its decorative inspiration.
repeat 72 cm

name: Paradiso
description:
A modern twist on an art-deco inspired floral using bird of paradise as a motif.
repeat 65 cm

name: Brass Monkeys
description:
Inspired by a slice of liver under a microscope, and combined with acetate and manipulated brass images. From the ‘Art vs Science’ range.
repeat 90 cm

name: Bloodsdream
description:
An imagining of what it would be like to be in the blood stream of a fairy tale creature, created with oil crayons and hand drawn sketches.
repeat 91 cm

name: Magnetic Attraction
description:
A damask created using my acetate drawings and by using iron filings and magnets to make patterns.
repeat 40 cm

name: Anenomous
description:
A playful and organic repeat of sea anemone on a sea bed.
repeat ? cm

name: Wowee
description:
Hand painted and hyper-stylized design from my 'Obnoxious Weeds' weeds range.
repeat 40 cm

name: Inner City
description:
I have grown up in the inner-city living in many terraces, this is my visual ode to the terrace and the inner city life.
repeat 75 cm

name: Pebbles
description:
After seeing an exhibition of the Canning Stock Route in Sydney , I fell in love and was inspired by the indigenous artists to produce a looser abstract design with a colourful palette.
repeat 41 cm

name: Paper Bird Forest - Birds & Trees
description:
This whimsical collection drew upon my natural surroundings and love of nature, especially birds and trees. I was heavily inspired by Akira Minagawa, Stig Lindberg and Josef Frank.
repeat 75 cm

name: Paper Bird Forest - Birds
description:
This whimsical collection drew upon my natural surroundings and love of nature, especially birds and trees. I was heavily inspired by Akira Minagawa, Stig Lindberg and Josef Frank.
repeat 75 cm

name: Paper Bird Forest - Trees
description:
This whimsical collection drew upon my natural surroundings and love of nature, especially birds and trees. I was heavily inspired by Akira Minagawa, Stig Lindberg and Josef Frank.
repeat 75 cm

name: Lucienne Tree - Blue
description:
This design stems a love & passion of 50's retro design period which has been translated into a textile repeat to be able to cover my collection of 50 – 60's furniture accumulation that furnishes our home. One of my greatest influences : Lucienne Day.
repeat 70 cm

name: Lucienne Tree - Red
description:
This design stems a love & passion of 50's retro design period which has been translated into a textile repeat to be able to cover my collection of 50 – 60's furniture accumulation that furnishes our home. One of my greatest influences : Lucienne Day.
repeat 70 cm

name: Purple Leaves - Folivm
description:
Satvrnalia explores ancient concepts of festive offerings and combines natural specimens with pagan symbolism. "FOLIVM" encompasses a wide range of plant offerings thought to appease and enlighten pagan gods.
repeat 200 cm

name: Botanic Rapture
description:
Botanic Rapture is exotic, Amazonian, tribal and neon. The kaleidoscopic floral print is infused with a beautiful neon colour palette. The dramatic dark base makes the blueberry, lime and tangerine hues burst and explode to stimulate your senses, depicting an oasis of a South American jungle.
repeat 60 cm

name: The Birth of The Sun
description:
This print depicts a Dreaming from the Wurundjeri people of Southern Victoria. An emu and a brolga get in to a fight over whose eggs are more brilliant. As the fight escalates the brolga tosses one of the emu’s eggs into the air. The egg hits a pile of sticks collected by the sky people and bursts in to flames spreading light over the land.
repeat 200 cm

name: How The Kangaroo Got Her Pouch
description:
This print depicts a Dreaming from the Wiradjuri people of central New South Wales. A mother kangaroo who is struggling to keep track of her joey crosses paths with a tired old wombat. The mother kangaroo is kind to the old wombat. In return the wombat, who is actually the spirit Biami in disguise gives her a dilly bag to keep her joey in.
repeat 200 cm

name: Tiddalik The Flood Maker
description:
This design depicts a Dreaming from the Gunai people of the Giplsand region in southeast Victoria. When a giant frog named Tiddalik wakes with an unquenchable thirst he manages to consume all of the water on the earth. The other animals realising the desperate situation ban together in an attempt to make the giant frog laugh and bring their water back.
repeat 200 cm

name: Escape From The Lighthouse
description:
A twisted children’s story in watercolour. This toile was also inspired by the stories and artwork of late surrealist artist, Leonora Carrington 1917 – 2011.
repeat 55 cm

name: The Lighthouse
description:
These children’s illustrations tell the story of a woman trapped in a lighthouse and her magical rescue. I created this toile design using watercolour. The style is magical realism and inspired by the late surrealist artist, Leonora Carrington 1917 – 2011.
repeat 40 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Overgrown
description:
Like ‘The Herbal’ this design is the result of a creative printmaking process. I created the background using the natural dyes from rosehip and black tea. The top layer is made up of lino prints motifs of persimmons, butterflies and lavender. It does not look as sweet as it sounds. I imagine this design digitally printed on silk to make an intriguing gown.
repeat 30 cm

name: Burning Flowers
description:
This is inspired by some flowers I saw in a garden on a very hot Summer’s day. Those flowers were so full of life that I felt they were trembling but burning in the sunshine. I then went back home and painted those passionate flowers by water-colour and then turned it to a fabric pattern I call ‘Burning Flowers’.
repeat 50 cm

name: Whirl
description:
This print is inspired by a combination of traditional Aboriginal paintings and one of my favourite themes, the butterfly. My friend gave me a book about Aboriginal arts, and I was amazed by the curving lines. I translated this style to create a world of butterflies in my imagination and my dreamland.
repeat 50 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Tiffany’s Flower
description:
This work was inspired by one of Tiffany’s glass art works. I was wondering, what it could look like if someone turned his works to watercolor painting. I’m not good at watercolor but one day I tried to paint a few flowers and then put them into repeat. They were lovely.
repeat 40 cm

name: Midsummer Night’s Dream
description:
This design was inspired by Shakespeare’s timeless fairytale and one of my favourite painting: Botticelli’s masterpiece Primavera. I think many people have a mid Summer night’s dream of her own. I have one too. It is mysterious, beautiful and dreamy.
repeat 50 cm

name: Panthera Noir
description:
Inspired by the exquisite fur of the black leopard - a colour variant of the leopard species that is primarily found within the dark, dense forest regions of South-East Asia. Its coat under minimal light appears almost completely black, however when seen in the light, it reveals both its smokey colouring and a subtle array of the spots and rosettes that are characteristic to its species. As a stylized re-creation of this unique specimen’s coat, this print incorporates a similarly deep colour palette, an arrangement of spots and rosettes, as well as photographic fur texture.
repeat 48 cm

name: Hanging Heliconia
description:
Throughout my trip I explored my creative senses. I first came across the Heliconia on the Road to Hana. I was immediately drawn to its unique shape. When designing prints I always concerntrate on the different contours and characteristics of my main muse and use them in an innovative and interesting way.
repeat 35 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Birds of Kaanapali
description:
Inspired by a recent trip to the Hawaiian islands, this print focuses on one of my experiences on the island of Maui. Kaanapali Beach located on the North west coast line of Maui, is not only the home to crystal clear ocean waters but also the most amazing plant life. The Birds of Paradise are not only a favourite of mine for their geometric shape and vibrant colours but are a vivid memory of my stay on Kaanapali Beach.
repeat 50 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: The Herbal
description:
This design is really a reflection of Elizabeth Blackwell’s illustrated volume ‘ A Curious Herbal’ 1737. It is a tribute to Australia’s long history of female botanical illustrators and celebrates my overgrown herb garden. I made illustrations of herbs and transferred them into a series of lino prints. I then arranged these original prints into pattern for the textile repeat.
repeat 60 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Damask
description:
This design is about fun, joy and happiness – the symbolism and hope that stems from the triumph of a sprouting flower in the harshest of surrounds. The brightness and sharpness of the colours in this pattern inspire new beginnings and positivism, which is conveyed through the intentionally more geometric rather than organic look to deliver a fresh take on the floral look.
repeat 12 cm

name: Park Guell
description:
The Park Guell print is a graphic interpretation of a specific mosaic at Gaudi’s Park Guell in Barcelona. The mosaic is beautiful and faded, but in places it still maintains its vibrancy and very saturated colour. I wanted to use that idea and create my own pop art style version of it.
repeat 18 cm

name: Mosaic
description:
This print was inspired by the amazing mosaic seating at Park Guell after a trip I took to Spain. The seating was a collaboration of Antoni Gaudi and Josep Maria Jujol that used both scrap and new tiles, and even coloured bottles and their own crockery. I loved the idea of taking a number of very different prints and combining them in a complimentary way.
repeat 18 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Ndebele
description:
Inspired by the artwork of the Ndebele tribes of South Africa, Zimbabwe and Botswana, The design ‘Ndebele’ takes reference of the distinctive black and white geometrical shapes combined with bright, curious colour palettes. Unlike any other type of Art, you will not find their work in Museums, or even in frames; but covering their whole houses, rondavels, cars, and fences. ‘Ndebele’ is an ode to their celebration of colour and print.
repeat 50 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Sunshowers
description:
‘Sunshowers’ is an all-over multi-directional design inspired by the abundant range, shape and colour of native African flowers. The florae arranged in ‘Sunshowers’ include; The Jade Plant, Flowering desert rose, The passion flower, Kaffir lily, African violet and the Fiddle-Leaf Fig, all of which are native to specific regions of the continent and provides a pastiche of exuberance as well as a lush, exotic, humid jungle vibe.
repeat 50 cm

name: Omo
description:
Aptly named ‘Omo’, the vivid, all-over design is inspired by the Mursi and Surma tribes of Ethiopia whom live along the Omo River. The tribes adorn themselves with flora and fauna to fashion spectacular headpieces and body accessories, while selecting bright mineral paints to decorate the skin, so wondering innocent, and beautiful. ‘Omo’ an interpretation of texture, form and colour, but importantly a representation of the joy, vibrancy and uninhibited thrill of the Mursi and Surma tribes.
repeat 67 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Pina Langur
description:
Inspired by the Golden Langur monkey - an endemic Indian species best known for its golden fur, dark face and long tail. It is primarily found leaping between the tall branches of the forest along the Assam-Bhutan border; collecting the fruits, flowers, leaves and seeds that make up its herbivorous diet. This print incorporates the Golden Langur as an illustrated specimen, framed by a selection of ginger flowers and sweet pineapples, as a colourful and creative profile of the animal and its diet.
repeat 34 cm

Buy a cushion in this print

name: Pixelated Dream
description:
I was inspired by a utopian place that does not exist in real life but in a dream. Geometric shape with soft colour represents artificial utopia.
repeat 22 cm

name: Sea Of Flora
description:
This print was in collaboration with Fashion Design Ultimo graduate, Joyce Cuda. Inspired by the delicate beauty of organic lines occurring in nature, this print incorporates flowers and petals that have been gently manipulated. All of these elements combined demonstrate artistically the softness of the flora.

name: Geometric Illusion

name: Elizabeth Bay Tulip
description:
Inspired by old-world floral displays in the beautiful historic house at Elizabeth Bay in Sydney. Detailed hand-drawn studies of the parrot tulip are presented in a fresh layout.
repeat 45 cm

name: Silver Leopard
description:
Whilst the leopard spot silhouettes were hand drawn, the texture was created from scanned images of a brindle cowhide. The Silver Leopard design tries to create a different, yet simple animal print using a firsthand contribution from nature itself.
repeat 42 cm

name: Luminous Hydrangea
description:
As its name suggests, these hydrangeas photographed in my parent’s garden have taken on a luminous quality. The design mimics the state of hydrangeas as they slowly deteriorate and lose the luminosity in their colour; some petals remaining radiant, and others fading as their corners curl.
repeat 56 cm

name: Hawaii Scarf - Large
description:
The Hawaii Scarf print follows current fashion trends of the return to scarf print designs. The versatility of scarf prints means they can be used as a repeated design or singularly as a scarf. This particular design juxtaposes the summer sunset of Waikiki with traditional bordered scarf designs.

name: Camellia
description:
The camellias, roses and peonies appearing in this print were all photographed in my parent’s garden. The flowers have taken on a layered, translucent state and an ice-like colouring. By transforming the flowers from their natural state, I have endeavoured to create a modern take on traditional florals that can only be produced using modern digital printing technologies.
